# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Coolify one-click deploy
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# When deploying through Coolify, all variables below are filled in
# automatically – no manual editing is required.
#
#   SERVICE_USER_MINIO          ← auto-generated root username
#   SERVICE_PASSWORD_MINIO      ← auto-generated root password
#   SERVICE_FQDN_MINIO_9000     ← auto-generated public domain for the S3 API (port 9000)
#   SERVICE_FQDN_MINIO_9001     ← auto-generated public domain for the web console (port 9001)
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Standalone docker compose (without Coolify)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your own values, then run:
#   docker compose up -d

# Root credentials
SERVICE_USER_MINIO=your-username-here
SERVICE_PASSWORD_MINIO=your-secure-password-here

# Public-facing URLs MinIO uses to build redirect and presigned URLs.
# Must be set to the URL your clients use to reach each endpoint.
SERVICE_FQDN_MINIO_9000=http://localhost:9000
SERVICE_FQDN_MINIO_9001=http://localhost:9001
